<TITLE> ZIA advised to cut all flights after 9pm </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 15 (bdnews24.com)  The Met office Thursday advised Zia International Airport to suspend all flights from 9pm until further notice as cyclone SIDR is expected to hit Bangladesh coast in the evening. Wing commander Saidul Hasan Khan, director of the Civil Aviation Authority of Bangladesh, told bdnews24.com: "As a precautionary measure, we've asked all concerned to tether the planes securely to ward off any accident in view of the cyclonic weather." Shah Amanat International Airport in Chittagong suspended its flight operations at 10pm Wednesday until otherwise told. Meteorologist Sujit Kumar Devsharma confirmed to bdnews24.com that they had advised ZIA to cut its flights after 9pm. He said they had alerted the control tower at ZIA too at noon. On possible flight suspension, Saidul Hasan Khan said: "No decision has yet been taken in this regard. In case we receive any news that cyclonic winds may strike the airport directly, we'll take necessary steps right away." bdnews24
